    "translations": {
      "en": {
        "summary": "The Prophet Muhammad (SAWW) commanded the Muslim community to love Imam Ali (AS), declaring that Ali's flesh and blood are his own. He warned that those from his nation who break the covenant regarding Ali and forget the Prophet's counsel about him will be cursed by Allah and will have no share of divine blessings. This hadith, narrated by the prominent companion Abu Sa'id al-Khudri, is a strong declaration of Ali's exalted status and the obligation to love and follow him.",
        "key_terms": {
          "لَحْمَهُ لَحْمِي": "His flesh is my flesh — a declaration of intimate kinship and unity between the Prophet and Ali",
          "عَهْدِي": "My covenant — the pact the Prophet established regarding Ali's authority",
          "وَصِيَّتِي": "My counsel/bequest — the Prophet's parting instructions regarding Ali",
          "خَلَاق": "Share of blessings — portion of divine favor and reward"
        },
        "seo_question": "What did the Prophet Muhammad say about loving Ali ibn Abi Talib?"
